    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Between the Conventions, Lieberman Is Topic A</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sozi Sozinho letter on Aug 8 article questions why it has taken so long for Jew to be on national party ticket and why no African-American has yet been chosen</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lieberman Will Run With Gore; First Jew on a Major U.S. Ticket'' (front page, Aug. 8):</p>
        <p>We should not celebrate the fact that Senator Joseph I. Lieberman is the first Jew to be on the ticket of a major party. We should be outraged that it has taken this long, and also that we have still not had an African-American candidate run on a major ticket.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Lieberman Will Run With Gore; First Jew on a Major U.S. Ticket'' (front page, Aug. 8):</p>
        <p>We should not celebrate the fact that Senator Joseph I. Lieberman is the first Jew to be on the ticket of a major party. We should be outraged that it has taken this long, and also that we have still not had an African-American candidate run on a major ticket.</p>
        <p>A diverse, rich country like ours needs leadership that reflects the composition of the country. Finally, we are moving in that direction.</p>
        <p>SOZI SOZINHO  New York, Aug. 8, 2000</p>
      </block>
